organic_results.title: The academic attainment of ethnic groups in Australia: A social psychological model
organic_results.snippet: Data from a sample of Australian students are used to estimate differences in the academic achievement of and the completion of secondary school by youths from Australian, English, Greek, and Italian backgrounds. The effects of ethnicity are relatively small, but there are important differences between the ethnic groups. Greek and Italian students have lower academic achievement than do Australian and English students, the social psychological support they receive for education is higher, and substantially more Greek and Italian …
